Dear {!Contact.FirstName},

Thank you for your inquiry.

An LLC formation is by default taxed as a pass-through entity, however it is definitely possible to change this tax-status to that of an S-Corporation. You can make this change by filing for S-corporation election with the IRS using forms 8832 and 2553.  

First you must file to be taxed as a corporation with form 8832.  

Then follow that with form 2553 to be taxed as an S-corporation.  

Both these forms can be downloaded free of charge at the IRS website, www.irs.gov, or you can search at www.google.com for the terms "8832" and "2553".  If you have further questions please contact a CPA or the IRS directly at 800.829.4933.  

